Wildfox - an essential element of celebrity style as seen on Vanessa Hudgens

Created by childhood friends Emily Faulstich and Kimberley Gordon, Wildfox Couture is known for vintage-inspired womenâ€™s knitwear. Wildfox tells a story of Emily and Kimberleyâ€™s generation and friendship, grabbing inspiration from their countless sleepovers, books, dreams, fairies and many other aspects from their childhood.

In 2007, the brand was officially established in Los Angeles along with world-renowned saxophonist Jimmy Sommers as CEO and President of Wildfox. With the help of Sommers, Wildfox has propelled into a highly recognizable brand through cultivating both a strong celebrity following and visibility in fashion press. With much success, Sommers has been able to break into a highly competitive market and quickly bring Wildfox to the pulse of fashion with their tees, sweats, tops, sunglasses and more.

Known for ultra soft fabrics and unique designs, Wildfox has developed into a full range of tops, bottoms, scarves and socks, denim and dresses. As of 2012, the brand has launched Wildfox Sun and Intimates. For a second season, Wildfox Swim launched in 2013. In 2012, Wildfox released a jewelry line, limited edition Daydream T collection and collaboration the popular shoe brand Jeffrey Campbell. Wildfox has even branched into the kids market, with their â€œlittle sisterâ€ adaptation of the womens line in 2009.

Wildfox has been featured on magazine covers such as Glamour and in articles in Cosmopolitan, Seventeen, InStyle, WWD, People, Us Weekly, etc. Not only does this brand get the attention of top magazines, but countless numbers of celebrities ranging from Beyonce to Victoria Beckham to Ashley Tisdale.

You can shop Wildfox clothing and accessories at high-end boutiques including Kitson and Neiman Marcus nationwide along with select department stores like Bloomingdaleâ€™s, Saks Fifth Avenue and Nordstrom. Wildfox is distributed in over 30 different countries.

As perfectly stated on the Wildfox website, â€œWildfox is for the dreamers, for the lovers, for skinny dippers, for barefoot explorers, for late night chocolate eaters; it is for people everywhere who believe in love and believe in themselves.â€

Our Story and Vision

We organize world-class beauty contests for women, men and children – “Ms. Elite Beauty Queen”, “Mrs. Elite Beauty Queen”, “Ms. Plus Size Elite Beauty Queen”, “Super Model Elite Beauty”, “Elite Beauty Business Queen of the World”, “Children Elite Beauty Talent /Princess / Prince”.

“This is the first beauty contest in the world, the idea of which is similar to the Victoria’s Secret show. Participants who have already won and proved themselves in various world-class beauty contests take part in it.

Our vision is creating magnificent shows, we increase good mood and joy, we cheer, we fascinate, we surprise both participants, and fans. We bring joy in the life of everyone. We put up our heart in realization of each action. We want to give the best to people and the planet on which we live.


Our vision is the most beautiful thing in this world is that, every day, every moment gives us something new and good. It is important to fill these moments with a sense of happiness, joy and love for yourself and your life.

Our vision is to gradually develop and become one of the leading organizers of beauty contests in the world.

About us

We at Lingerie Française collectively represent several centuries of outstanding savoir-faire, artistry, and leading-edge innovation. In fact, we essentially invented lingerie. Our member brands include Antigel, Antinéa, Aubade, Chantelle, Empreinte, Eprise, Implicite, Lise Charmel, LouLouisa Bracq, Maison Lejaby, Passionata, and Simone Pérèle.

The gold standard of quality, French lingerie has its many imitators (imitation, as they say, is the sincerest form of flattery), but only lingerie designed in France is truly French – hence the name of our blog. For more information on us and our member brands, visit us here:

We highly appreciate the financial support of DEFI, the Committee for the Development and Promotion of French Clothing, for development and launch of this blog.

 Community Wardrobe



Disposable fashion culture is the second biggest contributor to climate change in the world. We will build a culture of affordable preloved fashion, while investing the profits back into the community.


To build flourishing, resilient communities through social connection. 


We believe in community. We believe in preloved fashion. We believe in sustainability. We believe in social justice.


A problem shared is a problem halved. Share your unwanted clothing and accessories with us and we will invest the proceeds back into the community.


Partnerships in Action

Lentara developed a number of key inter-agency and corporate partnerships in order to support the growth of the retail strategy. As a part of a cutting-edge collaboration with RMIT school of Media and Communications, students designed a new identity for our retail stores to be trialled at a new site in Melbourne’s Northern Suburbs. The design concept features hand painted brush-typography and was a collaboration of five students.

The original community wardrobe concept included a mobile wardrobe which could collect and sell recycled goods at public events, food-truck festivals and potentially could be used in the event of a natural disaster with emergency material aid.
